cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on natural language processing and the use of deep neural networks to learn vector space embeddings of sentences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of supervised learning and the analysis of decision rules, which are common topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper is concerned with improving the performance of AI systems, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The authors also mention the use of sentence embeddings in computer vision (cs.CV) and the importance of structured datasets in better understanding AI systems, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
